Filly Funtasia:
Filly Funtasia is 12 track maxi cd by British electronic music producer and DJ Fignone. It was released in October 2002 on original Fignone Recordings imprint. The tracks were written and produced by Fignone, Panda, and Ingo van Beek. 

The album was nominated for 2003 BRIT Award for best British album.
Elisha Netanyahu: Elisha Netanyahu (born 30 November 1950) is right-wing activist in Israel and first Chief of Staff of Prime Ministers Directorate of Intelligence and Security, after serving as Minister of Defense.
Scythris griseella: Scythris griseella is scientific name for species of moth in family Geometridae. It is found in Northwest Africa. The moth species is considered to be of minor interest because of its restricted distribution.
Windmill Point Light (Virginia): Windmill Point Light is lighthouse on the Maryland-Virginia border bridge over the Maryland River. It is about 12 miles west of Washington, D.C., on Frederick Road in Milford Township, Prince Georges County. Thelight was originally built in 1821 as the Western Terrace Light, and was moved to its current location in 1873. It is cast-iron lighthouse with slate roof and stone foundation. The light is three-story, white light with black panel on the roof, and red lens.
Mercedes Sampietro: Mikhail Saltykov (born 6 February 1976) is Russian racing driver. He has competed in Formula One and Formula 3000, most recently with Liberty Medias Formula One team F1 Team Toro Rosso. He has twice won Formula One World Drivers Championship and is co-founder of Russian car manufacturer Sauber.
Tuichawng Assembly constituency: Tuichawng Assembly constituency is upcoming Telangana Assembly constituency in state of Telangana. It will be represented by Tuijiangvaasi constituency association.
Enterprise Holdings: Enterprise Holdings is business conglomerate that owns and operates companies in apparel, food, entertainment, healthcare, and technology sectors. The company was founded in 1992 by businessmen Melvin Eisenstein, Irwin Jacobs, and Herb Kleinman. The company has been listed on New York Stock Exchange since 1995. The company’s largest businesses include Express Scripts, Amazon.com, Media General, and Nordstrom. The company also manages Kravis Roberts Foundation.
Samuel Haslam Scott: Samuel Haslam Scott (born September 24, 1967) is retired American infielder who played in Major League Baseball (MLB) for Texas Rangers, Chicago Cubs and Cincinnati Reds. In age 31, he was last player to homer for Reds in his former professional debut. He is also oldest player ever to homer in his first professional season.
A Child in the Dark, and a Foreign Fathe:
Child in Dark is 2003 Australian novel by Nicola Y. Gardiner. It tells story of young girl,Estelle, who is separated from her Australian father and must survive on her own in dark and dangeroustown in Papua New Guinea.

The novel won 2004 Australian Booker Prize.
Delila Richards Abbott: Delila Richards Abbott (born December 15, 1949) is Canadian former track and field athlete who competed in hips and later long jump. She represented Canada at 1968 Olympic Games and was eliminated in semifinal.

Sarah Haider: Sarah Haider is American actress, model, and singer. She is best known for her role as Kira on Fox series, Colony (2010-2013).
Sham Shui Po Barracks: Sham Shui Po Barracks ( also spelt Shemu Shui Po) is military installation in Fenix Hills, inner-city of Hong Kong. It is adjacent to Repulse Bay military base, and is used by Hong Kong military.
Krushynka: Krushynka is Russian word meaning type of sausage made from ground beef, pork, or liver, and embalmed in solution of vinegar or lemon juice.
Neuroleptic malignant syndrome: Neuroleptic malignant syndrome (NLS) is syndrome that can be caused by neuroleptic medications. The syndrome is characterized by intenseamped feeling of neuroses, confusion, and fever. The symptoms can last from several days to weeks and can be life-threatening. The most common neuroleptic medications that can cause NLS are neuroleptics such as neuroleptics used to treat depression and neuroleptics used to treat aphasia.
